{"tid":1739924,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"彭斯: 香港暴力升溫令中美貿易戰談判雪上加霜","createTime":"2019-11-19T19:11:18.000Z","updateTime":"2019-11-20T01:03:31.000Z","uid":2748,"like":97,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":48,"replies":[{"pid":"fa75b00b4a2e55054eac7255ec54bc9e94c1d668","tid":1739924,"uid":2748,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-19T19:11:18.000Z","msg":"[url]<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-11-19/pence-says-hong-kong-violence-would-make-trade-deal-very-hard\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-11-19%2Fpence-says-hong-kong-violence-would-make-trade-deal-very-hard&d=UXFjm%2BDMXm%2Fj1yL9MgXeqM3u7Zzj2Sx3DhCMrptFZ9w%3D&h=6869d825\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-11-19/pence-says-hong-kong-violence-would-make-trade-deal-very-hard</a><br />\n[/url]<br />\n<br />\nVice President Mike Pence said Tuesday that it would be difficult for the U.S. to sign a trade agreement with China if demonstrations in Hong Kong are met with violence.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The president&rsquo;s made it clear it&rsquo;ll be very hard for us to do a deal with China if there&rsquo;s any violence or if that matter is not treated properly and humanely,&rdquo; Pence said during an interview with Indianapolis-based radio host Tony Katz.<br />\n<br />\nThe vice president said the U.S. is &ldquo;taking a strong stand with China&rdquo; while &ldquo;currently negotiating a phase-one deal.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nHundreds of Hong Kong demonstrators were hospitalized on Tuesday after a standoff with police, and protesters plan to block roads and disrupt rail service on Wednesday. The White House said in a statement on Monday that Chinese authorities should &ldquo;protect Hong Kong&rsquo;s freedom, legal system and democratic way of life,&rdquo; and Secretary of State Michael Pompeo said the U.S. is &ldquo;gravely concerned&rdquo; about rising violence in the city.<br />\n<br />\nBut President Donald Trump has spoken delicately about the protests while he attempts to close a deal with Chinese President Xi Jinping that may wind down the trade war with Beijing.<br />\n<br />\nTrump has yet to weigh in on an effort by Senate Republicans to pass legislation supporting the Hong Kong demonstrators, a measure that would risk angering Beijing.<br />\n<br />\nChinese officials expressed clear displeasure with the measure, calling it an improper intervention in their domestic affairs. The Foreign Ministry threatened &ldquo;strong countermeasures&rdquo; in response to the House&rsquo;s vote last week and repeated the threat as the Senate prepared to cast votes on Tuesday.<br />\n<br />\nThe bipartisan Senate bill would sanction Chinese officials who are found to have violated Hong Kong&rsquo;s &ldquo;freedoms and autonomy&rdquo; and require an annual review of Hong Kong&rsquo;s special status under U.S. law.<br />\n<br />\nTrump told reporters during a Cabinet meeting on Tuesday that China is &ldquo;going to have to make a deal that I like, if they don&rsquo;t that&rsquo;s it.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nBut the president added that he is &ldquo;very happy with China right now.&rdquo; He made no reference to the Hong Kong protests.<br />\n<br />\n&mdash; With assistance by Daniel Flatley"},{"pid":"d6ab23779e98175f0a6c9945cd5fd99bb40659f3","tid":1739924,"uid":335391,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-19T19:19:50.000Z","msg":"香港人權與民主法: 香港時間 6:25am<br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/1739917\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/1739917</a>"},{"pid":"672fbb8ba2f455d538d047c6a0724174703cb360","tid":1739924,"uid":195904,"like":6,"dislike":62,"score":-56,"citedBy":7,"replyTime":"2019-11-19T19:20:26.000Z","msg":"咁又點撚樣？你出手咪唔撚洗暴力升溫囉戇撚鳩"},{"pid":"1ef25d04f8e3e9d9bc725d0b56df00ec4e558e32","tid":1739924,"uid":159849,"like":123,"dislike":0,"score":123,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-19T19:24:0